text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia densiflora is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The dense pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.4 to 1.2 metres (1 to 4 ft) and produces yellow flowers.
